# CODEOWNERS — who must review changes to each path.
# Format: <path pattern>  <owner(s)>   (GitHub/GitLab-compatible)
# Replace the placeholder owners with real @users or @teams before enabling.

# --- Framework-wide (needs maintainer review; every team depends on these) ---
/shared/        @qa-framework-maintainers
/agents/        @qa-framework-maintainers
/README.md      @qa-framework-maintainers
/CONTRIBUTING.md @qa-framework-maintainers
/CODEOWNERS     @qa-framework-maintainers
/docs/          @qa-framework-maintainers

# --- Per-project (owned by the team that runs that project) ---
/projects/_template/   @qa-framework-maintainers
/projects/e-receive/   @team-e-receive
/projects/inventory/   @team-inventory

# When you add a project, add a line here mapping its folder to its owning team.
